# Faz 11: Security Hardening + Go-Live

## Goal

Pre-production security hardening. CSP strict. WAF tuning. External pentest + remediation. Dependency audit (Snyk). Secret rotation drill. Go-live checklist. Incident response runbook. KVKK compliance final review. Production launch.

## Bu fazın çalışma modeli (iterasyonlar)

`@61-phase-11-security-hardening` + **“Faz 11 — İterasyon N”**. İnsan/onay gerektiren adımlar (pentest firması, hukuk) için chat’te **bekleme durumu** açıkça işaretlensin.

### İterasyon 1 — Uygulama güvenlik başlıkları + CSP

**Hedef:** Next/Nest tarafında CSP (nonce/strict-dynamic), HSTS, `X-Frame-Options`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`; inline script temizliği planı.

**Bu iterasyonda yok:** Pentest raporu kapatma (İter 3).

**Stop:** [ ] Header’lar staging’de doğrulandı; [ ] ADR-0032 taslağı. PR/onay.

### İterasyon 2 — Bağımlılık + WAF + IAM + S3/DB sertleştirme

**Hedef:** `pnpm audit` + Snyk HIGH+; WAF managed+custom; IAM least-privilege review; S3 public block; DB parameter group hardening.

**Stop:** [ ] HIGH+ bulgu sayısı sıfır veya zamanlı waiver kaydı. PR/onay.

### İterasyon 3 — Pentest bulguları + secret rotation + backup/DR drill

**Hedef:** CRITICAL/HIGH remediate; JWT rotation drill staging; backup restore + DR dokümantasyonu (RTO/RPO).

**Stop:** [ ] Pentest temiz veya imzalı istisna planı; [ ] drill raporu. PR/onay.

### İterasyon 4 — Go-live checklist + runbook’lar + uyumluluk + launch protokolü

**Hedef:** `docs/runbooks/*` (6+), monitoring/alert testleri, KVKK envanter özeti, legal review tick, go-live günü protokolü, rollback testi.

**Stop:** Faz 11 Done Definition + post-launch Week 1 planı; roadmap işareti.

## Required Context

- `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` — complete security reference
- `docs/09_DEV_WORKFLOW.md` Bölüm 12 (Go-live) + Bölüm 13 (Incident response)

## Scope

### Security hardening

- **CSP (Content Security Policy)**: strict-dynamic + nonce, inline script elimination
- **HSTS**: max-age 63072000, includeSubDomains, preload
- **Security headers**: X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy
- **WAF rules**: AWS managed + custom (rate limit + geo block Türkiye-only if needed)
- **Dependency audit**: `pnpm audit`, Snyk full scan — all HIGH+ fixed
- **Secret rotation drill**: JWT secret rotate in prod (test rollback plan)
- **DB security**: parameter group hardened, audit log enabled
- **S3**: block public access verified, bucket policy restricts cross-account
- **IAM**: all roles least-privilege re-review

### External pentest

- Scope: production-like environment (staging)
- Engagement: external firm (2 hafta)
- Remediation priority:
  - CRITICAL → immediate fix, blocker for go-live
  - HIGH → fix before go-live
  - MEDIUM → fix within 4 week of go-live
  - LOW → backlog
- Final sign-off: clean pentest report or remediation plan signed

### Go-live checklist

- [ ] All CRITICAL + HIGH pentest findings remediated
- [ ] Load test final: 1000 concurrent, SLO met in staging production-like
- [ ] Backup + restore drill successful (point-in-time recovery tested)
- [ ] DR drill: restore snapshot to fresh region (documented RTO + RPO)
- [ ] Monitoring dashboards: CloudWatch + Sentry set up, PagerDuty on-call rotation
- [ ] Alerts: error rate, P95 latency, DB CPU, Redis memory, free disk, audit chain integrity
- [ ] Runbooks: incident response, common issue resolution, escalation tree
- [ ] KVKK: PII inventory + processing activity register (Varlık Envanteri + Veri İşleme Envanteri)
- [ ] Privacy policy + T&C live
- [ ] Legal review complete
- [ ] User communication: rollout schedule, support channels
- [ ] Training: admin team briefing on key features + incident response

### Incident response runbook

`docs/runbooks/` altında:
- Authentication outage
- Database failover
- Audit chain integrity breach
- Data exposure incident
- Ransomware / encryption attack
- Service degradation (partial outage)
- Account compromise (user account takeover suspected)

Her runbook:
- Symptoms (nasıl fark edilir)
- Initial triage (dakikalar içinde)
- Investigation (30-60 dk)
- Remediation (saatler)
- Post-incident (retrospective + ADR)

## Done Definition

- [ ] Pentest report: clean or documented remediation plan
- [ ] Secret rotation drill passed in staging (end-to-end)
- [ ] Backup restore drill: restore successful to fresh DB, data verified
- [ ] DR drill: cross-region restore < 4 hours RTO
- [ ] Monitoring: 100% SLI coverage, alerts tested (artificial failure triggered PagerDuty)
- [ ] Runbooks: 6+ written, team walkthrough done
- [ ] KVKK compliance: DPO sign-off (if applicable)
- [ ] Final load test: passed SLO
- [ ] Security champion review: checklist complete
- [ ] Go-live date agreed with stakeholders
- [ ] Rollback plan documented + tested

## Go-Live Day Protocol

1. **Freeze** — no merges to main 48 hours before
2. **Deploy** — off-peak hours, incremental traffic shift (5% → 25% → 50% → 100%)
3. **Monitor** — all dashboards watched, 2-hour war room
4. **Rollback trigger** — if error rate >1% for 10 min, revert
5. **Post-deploy** — 24-hour intensive monitoring, on-call rotation
6. **All-clear** — 48 hours stable → declare go-live complete

## Post-Launch (Week 1-2)

- Daily war room (30 min)
- User feedback collection (survey + interviews)
- Bug triage (escalate if hotfix needed)
- Performance monitoring (any regression?)
- Security monitoring (WAF rules firing? unexpected traffic?)

## Related ADRs

- ADR-0032: CSP policy details
- ADR-0033: WAF rule tuning (if project-specific)
- ADR-0034: Incident response escalation levels

